    "comment": "Rationale: Gephyrin is essential for the postsynaptic localization of glycine receptors (GlyR). Antisense knock-down of Gephyrin expression suppresses clustering of GlyR.\n\n29/3/2017 Pim\n- The experiment shows GlyR clusters at the membrane as opposed to intracellular GlyR hotspots. The membrane GlyR clusters are inferred to reflect GlycR clusters in the postsynaptic membrane.\n- The GlyR hotspots are presumed to be synaptic receptors by the authors and a er opposed to GPHN which is a marker for a postsynaptic specialization (see feedback thread).. Experimental description: ... sections of primary neurons from embryonic rat spinal cord... p. 746",
